-- Bool PARAMETER across a function boundary (slice 2b): `p` is inferred Bool from
-- its use as an `if` condition, and `choose` returns an Int.  The argument
-- (itself a Bool from a comparison) is passed as a uniform i64 word; the callee
-- treats it as a Bool when branching.
choose p = if p then 10 else 20
main = choose (3 < 7)
